# Technical Architecture

## Stack (Zero-Cost MVP Tier)

| Layer | Technology | Free Tier |
|-------|-----------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 14+ (App Router) | Vercel Hobby |
| Language | TypeScript (strict mode) | - |
| Database | Supabase PostgreSQL | 500MB, 50K rows |
| Auth | Supabase Auth | 50K MAU |
| Storage | Supabase Storage | 1GB |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui | OSS |
| Validation | Zod | OSS |
| State | React Server Components + Zustand (client) | OSS |

## Project Structure

```
src/
  app/                  # Next.js App Router (routes + layouts)
  components/
    ui/                 # Reusable primitives (shadcn/ui)
    features/           # Feature-specific composed components
  lib/
    supabase/           # Supabase client, helpers, RLS policies
    utils/              # Pure utility functions
    constants/          # App-wide constants and enums
    validations/        # Zod schemas (shared between client/server)
  hooks/                # Custom React hooks
  services/             # Business logic layer (server-side)
  types/                # Shared TypeScript types/interfaces
  config/               # Environment and app configuration
```

## Architecture Principles

1. **Feature-based colocation** — group related components, hooks, and logic by feature
2. **Server-first rendering** — default to RSC; use `"use client"` only when interactivity is required
3. **Thin route handlers** — API routes delegate to `services/` for business logic
4. **Single source of truth** — Zod schemas drive types, validation, and API contracts
5. **Environment-aware config** — all env vars accessed through `config/` with runtime validation
6. **No barrel exports** — import directly from the module file, avoid `index.ts` re-exports
7. **Max 300 lines per file** — split when approaching this limit

## Naming Conventions

- **Files**: `kebab-case.ts` for utilities, `PascalCase.tsx` for components
- **Types/Interfaces**: `PascalCase`, prefix interfaces only when needed for disambiguation
- **Functions**: `camelCase`, prefix hooks with `use`, server actions with action verb
- **Database**: `snake_case` for tables and columns (PostgreSQL convention)
- **Env vars**: `NEXT_PUBLIC_` prefix for client-exposed, `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE`
